{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":2023,"text":"It's wonderful to be back."},{"time":4666,"text":"I love this wonderful gathering."},{"time":7392,"text":"And you must be wondering, \"What on earth?"},{"time":9613,"text":"Have they put up the wrong slide?\""},{"time":11289,"text":"No, no."},{"time":13426,"text":"Look at this magnificent beast,"},{"time":17662,"text":"and ask the question: Who designed it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":23152,"text":"This is TED; this is\nTechnology, Entertainment, Design,"},{"time":27086,"text":"and there's a dairy cow."},{"time":28849,"text":"It's a quite wonderfully designed animal."},{"time":33104,"text":"And I was thinking,\nhow do I introduce this?"},{"time":35326,"text":"And I thought, well, maybe\nthat old doggerel by Joyce Kilmer,"},{"time":40000,"text":"you know: \"Poems are made by fools\nlike me, but only God can make a tree.\""},{"time":45004,"text":"And you might say,\n\"Well, God designed the cow.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":47692,"text":"But, of course, God got a lot of help."},{"time":51525,"text":"This is the ancestor of cattle."},{"time":53858,"text":"This is the aurochs."},{"time":56739,"text":"And it was designed by natural selection,"},{"time":58784,"text":"the process of natural selection,\nover many millions of years."},{"time":62719,"text":"And then it became domesticated,\nthousands of years ago."},{"time":67274,"text":"And human beings became its stewards,"},{"time":71947,"text":"and, without even knowing\nwhat they were doing,"},{"time":74201,"text":"they gradually redesigned it\nand redesigned it and redesigned it."},{"time":78521,"text":"And then more recently, they really began\nto do reverse engineering on this beast"},{"time":84783,"text":"and figure out just what\nthe parts were, how they worked"},{"time":87578,"text":"and how they might be optimized --\nhow they might be made better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":92220,"text":"Now, why am I talking about cows?"},{"time":96181,"text":"Because I want to say that\nmuch the same thing is true of religions."},{"time":101489,"text":"Religions are natural phenomena --\nthey're just as natural as cows."},{"time":106862,"text":"They have evolved over millennia."},{"time":111438,"text":"They have a biological base,\njust like the aurochs."},{"time":115798,"text":"They have become domesticated,"},{"time":117890,"text":"and human beings have been redesigning\ntheir religions for thousands of years."},{"time":124138,"text":"This is TED, and I want\nto talk about design."},{"time":128000,"text":"Because what I've been doing\nfor the last four years --"},{"time":130937,"text":"really since the first time you saw me --"},{"time":132981,"text":"some of you saw me at TED\nwhen I was talking about religion --"},{"time":136008,"text":"and in the last four years,"},{"time":137525,"text":"I've been working\njust about non-stop on this topic."},{"time":140961,"text":"And you might say it's about\nthe reverse engineering of religions."},{"time":146590,"text":"Now that very idea, I think,\nstrikes terror in many people,"},{"time":152177,"text":"or anger, or anxiety\nof one sort or another."},{"time":157743,"text":"And that is the spell\nthat I want to break."}]},{"cues":[{"time":160194,"text":"I want to say, no, religions\nare an important natural phenomenon."},{"time":163933,"text":"We should study them\nwith the same intensity"},{"time":167205,"text":"that we study all the other\nimportant natural phenomena,"},{"time":170396,"text":"like global warming, as we heard\nso eloquently last night from Al Gore."},{"time":175128,"text":"Today's religions are brilliantly\ndesigned -- brilliantly designed."},{"time":179620,"text":"They are immensely powerful\nsocial institutions"},{"time":183977,"text":"and many of their features\ncan be traced back to earlier features"},{"time":189281,"text":"that we can really make sense of\nby reverse engineering."},{"time":194333,"text":"And, as with the cow, there's a mixture\nof evolutionary design --"},{"time":199729,"text":"designed by natural selection itself --"},{"time":201722,"text":"and intelligent design --"},{"time":204853,"text":"more or less intelligent design --"},{"time":206691,"text":"and redesigned by human beings"},{"time":208413,"text":"who are trying\nto redesign their religions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":212564,"text":"You don't do book talks at TED,"},{"time":216168,"text":"but I'm going to have\njust one slide about my book,"},{"time":220316,"text":"because there is one message in it"},{"time":223013,"text":"which I think this group\nreally needs to hear."},{"time":225201,"text":"And I would be very interested\nto get your responses to this."},{"time":230050,"text":"It's the one policy proposal\nthat I make in the book,"},{"time":234719,"text":"at this time, when I claim\nnot to know enough about religion"},{"time":238106,"text":"to know what other\npolicy proposals to make."},{"time":240749,"text":"And it's one that echoes remarks\nthat you've heard already today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":245321,"text":"Here's my proposal,"},{"time":246504,"text":"I'm going to just take a couple\nof minutes to explain it:"},{"time":249458,"text":"Education on world religions\nfor all of our children --"},{"time":255026,"text":"in primary school, in high school,"},{"time":257193,"text":"in public schools, in private schools\nand in home schooling."},{"time":261521,"text":"So what I'm proposing is,"},{"time":263203,"text":"just as we require reading, writing,\narithmetic, American history,"},{"time":269087,"text":"so we should have a curriculum on facts\nabout all the religions of the world --"},{"time":276111,"text":"about their history,\nabout their creeds, about their texts,"},{"time":281000,"text":"their music, their symbolisms,\ntheir prohibitions, their requirements."},{"time":286994,"text":"And this should be presented\nfactually, straightforwardly,"},{"time":291837,"text":"with no particular spin,\nto all of the children in the country."},{"time":298507,"text":"And as long as you teach them that,"},{"time":301824,"text":"you can teach them anything else you like."},{"time":304713,"text":"That, I think, is maximal tolerance\nfor religious freedom."},{"time":309363,"text":"As long as you inform your children\nabout other religions,"},{"time":314000,"text":"then you may -- and as early as you like\nand whatever you like --"},{"time":317170,"text":"teach them whatever creed\nyou want them to learn."},{"time":320956,"text":"But also let them know\nabout other religions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":323616,"text":"Now, why do I say that?"},{"time":327365,"text":"Because democracy depends\non an informed citizenship."},{"time":334250,"text":"Informed consent is the very bedrock\nof our understanding of democracy."},{"time":341930,"text":"Misinformed consent is not worth it."},{"time":345000,"text":"It's like a coin flip;\nit doesn't count, really."},{"time":348247,"text":"Democracy depends on informed consent."},{"time":351000,"text":"This is the way we treat people\nas responsible adults."},{"time":356812,"text":"Now, children below the age of consent\nare a special case."},{"time":365608,"text":"Parents -- I'm going to use a word\nthat Pastor Rick just used --"},{"time":371223,"text":"parents are stewards of their children."},{"time":374159,"text":"They don't own them."},{"time":376286,"text":"You can't own your children."},{"time":378212,"text":"You have a responsibility to the world,"},{"time":381919,"text":"to the state, to them,\nto take care of them right."},{"time":387843,"text":"You may teach them whatever creed\nyou think is most important,"},{"time":393914,"text":"but I say you have a responsibility\nto let them be informed"},{"time":398764,"text":"about all the other creeds\nin the world, too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":402000,"text":"The reason I've taken this time\nis I've been fascinated to hear"},{"time":406492,"text":"some of the reactions to this."},{"time":409663,"text":"One reviewer for a Roman Catholic\nnewspaper called it \"totalitarian.\""},{"time":416849,"text":"It strikes me as practically libertarian."},{"time":421071,"text":"Is it totalitarian to require\nreading, writing and arithmetic?"},{"time":424118,"text":"I don't think so."},{"time":425301,"text":"All I'm saying is --"},{"time":427304,"text":"and facts, facts only;\nno values, just facts --"},{"time":433252,"text":"about all the world's religions."},{"time":436683,"text":"Another reviewer called it \"hilarious.\""},{"time":439900,"text":"Well, I'm really bothered by the fact"},{"time":443581,"text":"that anybody would think\nthat was hilarious."},{"time":446224,"text":"It seems to me to be such a plausible,"},{"time":450229,"text":"natural extension of the democratic\nprinciples we already have"},{"time":454649,"text":"that I'm shocked to think anybody\nwould find that just ridiculous."},{"time":460002,"text":"I know many religions"},{"time":463543,"text":"are so anxious about preserving the purity\nof their faith among their children"},{"time":470204,"text":"that they are intent on keeping\ntheir children ignorant of other faiths."},{"time":477145,"text":"I don't think that's defensible."},{"time":480184,"text":"But I'd really be pleased\nto get your answers on that --"},{"time":482842,"text":"any reactions to that -- later."}]},{"cues":[{"time":484393,"text":"But now I'm going to move on."},{"time":486540,"text":"Back to the cow."},{"time":488000,"text":"This picture, which I pulled\noff the web --"},{"time":491388,"text":"the fellow on the left is really\nan important part of this picture."},{"time":494717,"text":"That's the steward."},{"time":496305,"text":"Cows couldn't live without human\nstewards -- they're domesticated."},{"time":501838,"text":"They're a sort of ectosymbiont."},{"time":505132,"text":"They depend on us for their survival."},{"time":510380,"text":"And Pastor Rick\nwas just talking about sheep."},{"time":513747,"text":"I'm going to talk about sheep, too."},{"time":515470,"text":"There's a lot of serendipitous\nconvergence here."},{"time":519007,"text":"How clever it was of sheep\nto acquire shepherds!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":522940,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":525297,"text":"Think of what this got them."},{"time":527438,"text":"They could outsource all their problems:"},{"time":530000,"text":"protection from predators,\nfood-finding ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":532635,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":533666,"text":"... health maintenance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":535025,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":537712,"text":"The only cost in most flocks --\nnot even this -- a loss of free mating."},{"time":544665,"text":"What a deal!"},{"time":546673,"text":"\"How clever of sheep!\" you might say."},{"time":548573,"text":"Except, of course,\nit wasn't the sheep's cleverness."},{"time":551098,"text":"We all know sheep are not exactly rocket\nscientists -- they're not very smart."},{"time":556427,"text":"It wasn't the cleverness\nof the sheep at all."},{"time":558574,"text":"They were clueless."},{"time":561201,"text":"But it was a very clever move."},{"time":563159,"text":"Whose clever move was it?"},{"time":564506,"text":"It was the clever move\nof natural selection itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":568818,"text":"Francis Crick, the co-discoverer\nof the structure of DNA"},{"time":574625,"text":"with Jim Watson,"},{"time":576412,"text":"once joked about what he called\nOrgel's Second Rule."},{"time":579578,"text":"Leslie Orgel is a molecular\nbiologist, brilliant guy,"},{"time":584853,"text":"and Orgel's Second Rule is:"},{"time":586247,"text":"Evolution is cleverer than you are."},{"time":589960,"text":"Now, that is not Intelligent Design --\nnot from Francis Crick."},{"time":596479,"text":"Evolution is cleverer than you are."},{"time":598194,"text":"If you understand Orgel's Second Rule,\nthen you understand"},{"time":601352,"text":"why the Intelligent Design movement\nis basically a hoax."}]},{"cues":[{"time":608216,"text":"The designs discovered\nby the process of natural selection"},{"time":612654,"text":"are brilliant, unbelievably brilliant."},{"time":615058,"text":"Again and again biologists are fascinated\nwith the brilliance of what's discovered."},{"time":620283,"text":"But the process itself is without purpose,"},{"time":623472,"text":"without foresight, without design."},{"time":626358,"text":"When I was here four years ago,"},{"time":627913,"text":"I told the story about an ant\nclimbing a blade of grass."},{"time":630858,"text":"And why the ant was doing it\nwas because its brain had been infected"},{"time":634748,"text":"with a lancet fluke that was needed\nto get into the belly of a sheep or a cow"},{"time":639944,"text":"in order to reproduce."},{"time":642342,"text":"So it was sort of a spooky story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":644000,"text":"And I think some people\nmay have misunderstood."},{"time":646770,"text":"Lancet flukes aren't smart."},{"time":648874,"text":"I submit that the intelligence\nof a lancet fluke is down there,"},{"time":653132,"text":"somewhere between petunia and carrot."},{"time":655336,"text":"They're not really bright.\nThey don't have to be."},{"time":657662,"text":"The lesson we learn from this is:"},{"time":659273,"text":"you don't have to have a mind\nto be a beneficiary."},{"time":662797,"text":"The design is there in nature,\nbut it's not in anybody's head."},{"time":667750,"text":"It doesn't have to be."},{"time":669000,"text":"That's the way evolution works."},{"time":671635,"text":"Question: Was domestication\ngood for sheep?"},{"time":674223,"text":"It was great for their genetic fitness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":676294,"text":"And here I want to remind you\nof a wonderful point"},{"time":679000,"text":"that Paul MacCready made\nat TED three years ago."},{"time":682997,"text":"Here's what he said:"},{"time":685012,"text":"\"Ten thousand years ago,\nat the dawn of agriculture,"},{"time":687667,"text":"human population, plus livestock and pets,"},{"time":690103,"text":"was approximately a tenth of one percent\nof the terrestrial vertebrate landmass.\""},{"time":695519,"text":"That was just 10,000 years ago."},{"time":698234,"text":"Yesterday, in biological terms."},{"time":700708,"text":"What is it today? Does anybody\nremember what he told us?"},{"time":704167,"text":"98 percent."},{"time":706639,"text":"That is what we have done on this planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":709456,"text":"Now, I talked to Paul afterwards --\nI wanted to check to find out"},{"time":712549,"text":"how he'd calculated this, and get\nthe sources and so forth --"},{"time":715446,"text":"and he also gave me a paper\nthat he had written on this."},{"time":718169,"text":"And there was a passage in it\nwhich he did not present here"},{"time":721015,"text":"and I think it is so good,\nI'm going to read it to you:"},{"time":723634,"text":"\"Over billions of years\non a unique sphere,"},{"time":726798,"text":"chance has painted\na thin covering of life:"},{"time":729663,"text":"complex, improbable,\nwonderful and fragile."},{"time":733050,"text":"Suddenly, we humans --\na recently arrived species"},{"time":736000,"text":"no longer subject to the checks\nand balances inherent in nature --"},{"time":739472,"text":"have grown in population,\ntechnology and intelligence"},{"time":742314,"text":"to a position of terrible power."},{"time":744281,"text":"We now wield the paintbrush.\""},{"time":747358,"text":"We heard about the atmosphere\nas a thin layer of varnish."},{"time":750771,"text":"Life itself is just a thin coat\nof paint on this planet."},{"time":754830,"text":"And we're the ones\nthat hold the paintbrush."},{"time":757576,"text":"And how can we do that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":759179,"text":"The key to our domination\nof the planet is culture."},{"time":763557,"text":"And the key to culture is religion."},{"time":766990,"text":"Suppose Martian scientists came to Earth."},{"time":769958,"text":"They would be puzzled by many things."},{"time":773683,"text":"Anybody know what this is?\nI'll tell you what it is."},{"time":777562,"text":"This is a million people gathering\non the banks of the Ganges in 2001,"},{"time":782879,"text":"perhaps the largest single gathering\nof human beings ever,"},{"time":786365,"text":"as seen from satellite photograph."},{"time":788597,"text":"Here's a big crowd."},{"time":789773,"text":"Here's another crowd in Mecca."},{"time":792153,"text":"Martians would be amazed by this."},{"time":794985,"text":"They'd want to know how it originated,"},{"time":796831,"text":"what it was for\nand how it perpetuates itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":800061,"text":"Actually, I'm going to pass over this."},{"time":803156,"text":"The ant isn't alone."},{"time":804435,"text":"There's all sorts of wonderful cases\nof species which -- in that case --"},{"time":811617,"text":"A parasite gets into a mouse\nand needs to get into the belly of a cat."},{"time":815347,"text":"And it turns the mouse\ninto Mighty Mouse, makes it fearless,"},{"time":818232,"text":"so it runs out in the open,\nwhere it'll be eaten by a cat."},{"time":821039,"text":"True story."},{"time":822730,"text":"In other words, we have these hijackers --"},{"time":824766,"text":"you've seen this slide before,\nfrom four years ago --"},{"time":827274,"text":"a parasite that infects the brain\nand induces even suicidal behavior,"},{"time":831184,"text":"on behalf of a cause\nother than one's own genetic fitness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":835314,"text":"Does that ever happen to us?"},{"time":837562,"text":"Yes, it does -- quite wonderfully."},{"time":842102,"text":"The Arabic word \"Islam\"\nmeans \"submission.\""},{"time":844133,"text":"It means \"surrender of self-interest\nto the will of Allah.\""},{"time":847617,"text":"But I'm not just talking about Islam."},{"time":849424,"text":"I'm talking also about Christianity."},{"time":851597,"text":"This is a parchment music page\nthat I found in a Paris bookstall"},{"time":854959,"text":"50 years ago."},{"time":856251,"text":"And on it, it says, in Latin:"},{"time":859528,"text":"\"Semen est verbum Dei.\nSator autem Christus.\""},{"time":862512,"text":"The word of God is the seed\nand the sower of the seed is Christ."},{"time":866418,"text":"Same idea. Well, not quite."},{"time":868621,"text":"But in fact, Christians, too ..."},{"time":873297,"text":"glory in the fact\nthat they have surrendered to God."},{"time":876956,"text":"I'll give you a few quotes."},{"time":878328,"text":"\"The heart of worship is surrender."},{"time":881173,"text":"Surrendered people obey God's words,\neven if it doesn't make sense.\""},{"time":886182,"text":"Those words are by Rick Warren."},{"time":888802,"text":"Those are from \"The Purpose Driven Life.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":891898,"text":"And I want to turn now, briefly,\nto talk about that book, which I've read."},{"time":895548,"text":"You've all got a copy,"},{"time":896915,"text":"and you've just heard the man."},{"time":899131,"text":"And what I want to do now\nis say a bit about this book"},{"time":902862,"text":"from the design standpoint,"},{"time":904321,"text":"because I think it's actually\na brilliant book."},{"time":908369,"text":"First of all, the goal -- and you\nheard just now what the goal is --"},{"time":911608,"text":"it's to bring purpose to the lives\nof millions, and he has succeeded."},{"time":914943,"text":"Is it a good goal? In itself, I'm sure\nwe all agree, it is a wonderful goal."},{"time":918739,"text":"He's absolutely right."},{"time":919914,"text":"There are lots of people out there\nwho don't have purpose in their life,"},{"time":923746,"text":"and bringing purpose to their life\nis a wonderful goal."},{"time":926580,"text":"I give him an A+ on this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":928196,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":930044,"text":"Is the goal achieved?"},{"time":933822,"text":"Yes."},{"time":936266,"text":"Thirty million copies of this book."},{"time":940519,"text":"Al Gore, eat your heart out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":942000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":945681,"text":"Just exactly what Al is trying\nto do, Rick is doing."},{"time":949326,"text":"This is a fantastic achievement."},{"time":953028,"text":"And the means -- how does he do it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":957000,"text":"It's a brilliant redesign\nof traditional religious themes --"},{"time":960000,"text":"updating them, quietly dropping\nobsolete features,"},{"time":963325,"text":"putting new interpretations\non other features."},{"time":965507,"text":"This is the evolution of religion that's\nbeen going on for thousands of years,"},{"time":969222,"text":"and he's just the latest\nbrilliant practitioner of it."},{"time":973833,"text":"I don't have to tell you this;\nyou just heard the man."},{"time":976413,"text":"Excellent insights into human psychology,\nwise advice on every page."},{"time":982079,"text":"Moreover, he invites us\nto look under the hood."},{"time":985431,"text":"I really appreciated that."},{"time":986804,"text":"For instance, he has an appendix\nwhere he explains"},{"time":989272,"text":"his choice of translations\nof different Bible verses."},{"time":992999,"text":"The book is clear, vivid, accessible,\nbeautifully formatted."},{"time":999323,"text":"Just enough repetition."},{"time":1001528,"text":"That's really important."},{"time":1003568,"text":"Every time you read it or say it,\nyou make another copy in your brain."},{"time":1008871,"text":"Every time you read it or say it,\nyou make another copy in your brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1012640,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1013672,"text":"With me, everybody --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1014940,"text":"(Audience and Dan Dennett)\nEvery time you read it or say it,"},{"time":1017940,"text":"you make another copy in your brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1020265,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1021450,"text":"And now we come to my problem."},{"time":1023767,"text":"Because I'm absolutely sincere\nin my appreciation"},{"time":1027000,"text":"of all that I said about this book."},{"time":1029560,"text":"But I wish it were better."},{"time":1031242,"text":"I have some problems with the book."},{"time":1033202,"text":"And it would just be insincere of me\nnot to address those problems."},{"time":1037346,"text":"I wish he could do this with a revision,"},{"time":1041133,"text":"a Mark 2 version of his book."},{"time":1045600,"text":"\"The truth will set you free.\""},{"time":1047536,"text":"That's what it says in the Bible,"},{"time":1049467,"text":"and it's something\nthat I want to live by, too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1052418,"text":"My problem is, some of the bits in it\nI don't think are true."},{"time":1057748,"text":"Now some of this\nis a difference of opinion."},{"time":1062173,"text":"And that's not my main complaint,\nthat's worth mentioning."},{"time":1065062,"text":"Here's a passage -- it's very much\nwhat he said, anyway:"},{"time":1068275,"text":"\"If there was no God\nwe would all be accidents,"},{"time":1070798,"text":"the result of astronomical\nrandom chance in the Universe."},{"time":1073933,"text":"You could stop reading this book\nbecause life would have no purpose"},{"time":1077335,"text":"or meaning or significance."},{"time":1078843,"text":"There would be no right or wrong"},{"time":1080449,"text":"and no hope beyond\nyour brief years on Earth.\""},{"time":1082619,"text":"Now, I just do not believe that."},{"time":1084552,"text":"By the way, I find -- Homer Groening's\nfilm presented a beautiful alternative"},{"time":1090756,"text":"to that very claim."},{"time":1092861,"text":"Yes, there is meaning and a reason\nfor right or wrong."},{"time":1096290,"text":"We don't need a belief in God\nto be good or to have meaning in us."},{"time":1102548,"text":"But that, as I said,\nis just a difference of opinion."},{"time":1106833,"text":"That's not what I'm really worried about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1109650,"text":"How about this: \"God designed\nthis planet's environment"},{"time":1112603,"text":"just so we could live in it.\""},{"time":1115213,"text":"I'm afraid that a lot of people\ntake that sentiment to mean"},{"time":1119679,"text":"that we don't have to do\nthe sorts of things"},{"time":1122323,"text":"that Al Gore is trying so hard\nto get us to do."},{"time":1124735,"text":"I am not happy with that sentiment at all."},{"time":1127000,"text":"And then I find this: \"All the evidence\navailable in the biological sciences"},{"time":1131596,"text":"supports the core proposition that\nthe cosmos is a specially designed whole"},{"time":1135304,"text":"with life and mankind\nas its fundamental goal and purpose,"},{"time":1138607,"text":"a whole in which all facets\nof reality have their meaning"},{"time":1141315,"text":"and explanation in this central fact.\""},{"time":1143356,"text":"Well, that's Michael Denton.\nHe's a creationist."},{"time":1146833,"text":"And here, I think, \"Wait a minute.\"\nI read this again."},{"time":1150000,"text":"I read it three or four times and I think,"},{"time":1152063,"text":"\"Is he really endorsing\nIntelligent Design?"},{"time":1154631,"text":"Is he endorsing creationism here?\""},{"time":1156642,"text":"And you can't tell."},{"time":1157901,"text":"So I'm sort of thinking,\n\"Well, I don't know,"},{"time":1160030,"text":"I don't know if I want\nto get upset with this yet.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1162451,"text":"But then I read on, and I read this:\n\"First, Noah had never seen rain,"},{"time":1166559,"text":"because prior to the Flood, God irrigated\nthe earth from the ground up.\""},{"time":1171614,"text":"I wish that sentence weren't in there,\nbecause I think it is false."},{"time":1176537,"text":"And I think that thinking this way\nabout the history of the planet,"},{"time":1179728,"text":"after we've just been hearing\nabout the history of the planet"},{"time":1183475,"text":"over millions of years,"},{"time":1186631,"text":"discourages people\nfrom scientific understanding."},{"time":1189842,"text":"Now, Rick Warren uses scientific terms"},{"time":1196411,"text":"and scientific factoids and information\nin a very interesting way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1200541,"text":"Here's one: \"God deliberately shaped\nand formed you to serve him"},{"time":1203929,"text":"in a way that makes your ministry unique."},{"time":1205998,"text":"He carefully mixed the DNA cocktail\nthat created you.\""},{"time":1212808,"text":"I think that's false."},{"time":1215000,"text":"Now, maybe we want to treat it\nas metaphorical."},{"time":1218618,"text":"Here's another one: \"For instance,\nyour brain can store 100 trillion facts."},{"time":1222221,"text":"Your mind can handle\n15,000 decisions a second.\""},{"time":1225964,"text":"Well, it would be interesting\nto find the interpretation"},{"time":1228662,"text":"where I would accept that."},{"time":1230067,"text":"There might be some way\nof treating that as true."},{"time":1233511,"text":"\"Anthropologists have noted\nthat worship is a universal urge,"},{"time":1236843,"text":"hardwired by God into\nthe very fiber of our being --"},{"time":1239522,"text":"an inbuilt need to connect with God.\""},{"time":1243392,"text":"Well, the sense of which I agree with him,"},{"time":1245584,"text":"except I think it has\nan evolutionary explanation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1247988,"text":"And what I find\ndeeply troubling in this book"},{"time":1251833,"text":"is that he seems to be arguing\nthat if you want to be moral,"},{"time":1255610,"text":"if you want to have meaning in your life,"},{"time":1257803,"text":"you have to be an Intelligent Designer,"},{"time":1260294,"text":"you have to deny the theory of evolution\nby natural selection."},{"time":1263839,"text":"And I think, on the contrary,"},{"time":1265342,"text":"that it is very important\nto solving the world's problems"},{"time":1268307,"text":"that we take evolutionary\nbiology seriously."},{"time":1272427,"text":"Whose truth are we going to listen to?"},{"time":1275649,"text":"Well, this is from\n\"The Purpose Driven Life\":"},{"time":1278225,"text":"\"The Bible must become\nthe authoritative standard for my life:"},{"time":1281542,"text":"the compass I rely on for direction,"},{"time":1283305,"text":"the counsel I listen to\nfor making wise decisions,"},{"time":1286146,"text":"and the benchmark I use\nfor evaluating everything.\""},{"time":1289458,"text":"Well maybe, OK, but what's going\nto follow from this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1293869,"text":"And here's one that does concern me."},{"time":1297463,"text":"Remember I quoted him\nbefore with this line:"},{"time":1299840,"text":"\"Surrendered people obey God's word,\neven if it doesn't make sense.\""},{"time":1305335,"text":"And that's a problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1309843,"text":"(Sighs)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1310867,"text":"\"Don't ever argue with the Devil."},{"time":1312535,"text":"He's better at arguing than you are,"},{"time":1314290,"text":"having had thousands\nof years to practice.\""},{"time":1316700,"text":"Now, Rick Warren\ndidn't invent this clever move."},{"time":1320951,"text":"It's an old move."},{"time":1322649,"text":"It's a very clever\nadaptation of religions."},{"time":1325224,"text":"It's a wild card for disarming\nany reasonable criticism."},{"time":1330546,"text":"\"You don't like my interpretation?"},{"time":1332292,"text":"You've got a reasonable objection to it?"},{"time":1334268,"text":"Don't listen, don't listen!"},{"time":1336321,"text":"That's the Devil speaking.\""},{"time":1339185,"text":"This discourages the sort\nof reasoning citizenship"},{"time":1344810,"text":"it seems to me that we want to have."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1347668,"text":"I've got one more problem,\nthen I'm through."},{"time":1350298,"text":"And I'd really like to get\na response if Rick is able to do it."},{"time":1355593,"text":"\"In the Great Commission, Jesus said,"},{"time":1357396,"text":"'Go to all people of all nations\nand make them my disciples."},{"time":1360282,"text":"Baptize them in the name of the Father,\nthe Son and the Holy Spirit,"},{"time":1363521,"text":"and teach them to do\neverything I've told you.'\""},{"time":1365812,"text":"The Bible says Jesus is the only one\nwho can save the world."},{"time":1369930,"text":"We've seen many wonderful maps\nof the world in the last day or so."},{"time":1374297,"text":"Here's one, not as beautiful\nas the others;"},{"time":1376647,"text":"it simply shows\nthe religions of the world."},{"time":1380066,"text":"Here's one that shows the sort of current\nbreakdown of the different religions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1387099,"text":"Do we really want to commit ourselves"},{"time":1391633,"text":"to engulfing all the other religions,"},{"time":1396577,"text":"when their holy books are telling them,"},{"time":1399967,"text":"\"Don't listen to the other side,\nthat's just Satan talking!\"?"},{"time":1404450,"text":"It seems to me that\nthat's a very problematic ship"},{"time":1410811,"text":"to get on for the future."},{"time":1413750,"text":"I found this sign as I was driving\nto Maine recently,"},{"time":1418000,"text":"in front of a church:\n\"Good without God becomes zero.\""},{"time":1420691,"text":"Sort of cute."},{"time":1422205,"text":"A very clever little meme."},{"time":1426589,"text":"I don't believe it and I think this idea,\npopular as it is --"},{"time":1432217,"text":"not in this guise, but in general --"},{"time":1434332,"text":"is itself one of the main\nproblems that we face."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1437609,"text":"If you are like me, you know\nmany wonderful, committed, engaged"},{"time":1444304,"text":"atheists, agnostics, who are being\nvery good without God."},{"time":1450000,"text":"And you also know many religious people\nwho hide behind their sanctity"},{"time":1455729,"text":"instead of doing good works."},{"time":1457959,"text":"So, I wish we could drop this meme."},{"time":1461578,"text":"I wish this meme would go extinct."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1463595,"text":"Thanks very much for your attention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1465366,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}